    </div>
    <div class="comment-right"><p>Hi Kacper,<br />
My husband loves spicy noodles.<br />
He boils water in kettle at work, takes out his lunchbox with tight fitting lid &amp; places in his pack of noodles.(Ramen style)<br />
After adding seasoning, he mixes through a tin of flavoured tuna. A piece of fruit usually puts out the fire.<br />
You can vary this any no. of ways.<br />
I&#8217;m  a vege freak.<br />
I would add a small parcel of grated carrot, or a block of frozen spinach, maybe a handful of peas, avocado is always yummy, grated cheese, shredded cabbage etc.etc.<br />
I tried some sardines today and they were surprisingly tasty and a little different (make sure you have some breath freshners on hand. LOL<br />
All the best &amp; happy lunching.
