    </div>
    <div class="comment-right"><p>A good thermos is also a great option for those who do not have access to a microwave. Soups, chili, lasagna&#8230;anything can go into a thermos.  I heat the food extra hot at home before I put it in the thermos, and I also pre-heat the thermos by putting boiling water in first for a few minutes, then dumping the water out and drying it (if necessary.) This is how my mom would put soup in our lunch on cold days at school.
